Help Type: topic
Topic: task

Task Guide

Create an archive from a source:
  spinedigest create book.sdpub ./book.epub
  spinedigest status book.sdpub

Estimate before expensive build:
  spinedigest estimate book.sdpub --stage summary
  spinedigest estimate book.sdpub --stage graph --json

Build scoped knowledge:
  spinedigest build book.sdpub --stage graph --chapter 3 --confirm
  spinedigest build book.sdpub --stage summary --chapter 3 --confirm

Browse an existing archive:
  spinedigest status book.sdpub
  spinedigest index book.sdpub
  spinedigest chapter tree book.sdpub --json
  spinedigest list book.sdpub --type chapter
  spinedigest list book.sdpub --type node --chapter 3

Understand a chapter as wiki topology:
  spinedigest page book.sdpub chapter:3 --json
  Inspect `nodeGroups` to choose the relevant knowledge nodes.
  spinedigest page book.sdpub node:84

Search and read:
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "RAG" --type node
  spinedigest grep book.sdpub "exact source phrase"
  spinedigest page book.sdpub node:84
  spinedigest read book.sdpub chapter:3

Navigate graph knowledge:
  spinedigest links book.sdpub node:84
  spinedigest backlinks book.sdpub node:84
  spinedigest related book.sdpub node:84
  spinedigest path book.sdpub node:84 node:120 --chapter 3

Pack deterministic context:
  spinedigest pack book.sdpub node:84 --budget 5000
  spinedigest pack book.sdpub node:84 --budget 5000 --json

Export projections:
  spinedigest export book.sdpub --output-format markdown --output digest.md
  spinedigest export book.sdpub --output-format epub --output digest.epub

Lower-level maintenance:
  Use `spinedigest chapter tree` to inspect table-of-contents hierarchy. Use `spinedigest meta`, `spinedigest cover`, `spinedigest chapter tree apply`, and other mutating `chapter` actions only when you need metadata mutation, cover extraction, or chapter tree edits.
